  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: On Send transaction screen: if tap on Advanced switch then Transaction Fee field is shown behind keyboard, so user can't see it.\r\n\r\nIt happens if keyboard was already opened, e.g. if user filled in Amount field and then taps on Advanced switch. On both iOS (iphone 6s) and Android (Galaxy S6)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAfter user taps on Advanced switch: Transaction Fee field is visible to the user (no need to scroll to it)\r\n![screenshot_20180214-162741](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/36208698-bec44564-11aa-11e8-897a-8bea8fa092cd.png)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAfter user taps on Advanced switch: only arrow in the Advanced switch changes its direction. Because of the opened keyboard new field Transaction Fee is not shown\r\n![screenshot_20180214-162732](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/36208718-c927de6c-11aa-11e8-8218-723cd72e0750.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nFrom 00:17 https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/7699096/sessions/31/?accessToken=TGN2NVSPbWChZTBpsLqY8ncn8gk\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- Send transaction\r\n- Tap in amount field and type some amount. As a result, keyboard is opened\r\n- Tap on Advanced switch to show Transaction Fee field\r\n- Check that you can see Transaction Fee field and tap on it without scrolling the screen\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.13 and nightly build Feb 14\r\n* Operating System: iOS (iphone 6s) and Android (Galaxy S6)\r\n",
